Method to aggregate peptides into proteins with the iterative approach with use of parallelism.

aggIterParallel.Rd

Method to aggregate peptides into proteins with the iterative approach with use of parallelism.

aggIterParallel(
  qPepData,
  X,
  conditions = NULL,
  init.method = "Sum",
  method = "Mean",
  n = NULL
)

Arguments

qPepData

A matrix of intensities of peptides.
X

An adjacency matrix in which lines and columns correspond respectively to peptides and proteins.
conditions

xxxx
init.method

The method used to initialize the iterative algotirhm. Default is 'Sum'.
method

The method used for xxx. Default value is 'Mean'.
n

xxxx

Value

A matrix of intensities of proteins

Author

Samuel Wieczorek

Examples

library(doParallel)

#> Warning: package ‘doParallel’ was built under R version 4.0.2

library(QFeatures)
utils::data(Exp1_R25_pept, package='DAPARdata2')
obj <- Exp1_R25_pept[1:1000,]
obj <- addListAdjacencyMatrices(obj, 2)
X <- as.matrix(GetAdjMat(obj[[2]], 'all'))
conditions <- SummarizedExperiment::colData(obj)$Condition
aggIterParallel(assay(obj,2), X, conditions)
